SIMPLE: edged
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: edged
<hw>edged</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>having a specified kind
of border or edge; <as>as, a black-<ex>edged</ex> card; dried sweat left
salt-<ex>edged</ex> patches</as>.</def>
<mark>[Postpositional]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>having a cutting edge or especially an edge or edges
as specified; often used in combination; <as>as, a dull-<ex>edged</ex>
blade</as>. Opposite of <ant>edgeless</ant>.</def>
<mark>[Postpositional]</mark> ⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>having a biting effect, implying criticism; -- used
of words or language; <as>as, <ex>edged</ex> satire</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> cutting, harsh, sharp, sharp-worded,
stinging.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Edgeless</ent>⟦br⟧
